{
  "stem": "22972.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The school year ends the week before Easter, you have a three week vacation, and then the new school year starts, beginning of April, something like that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was customary then, as it is in America now, to have a class picnic.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our teacher, this wonderful professor Neumann, who let it be known that she didn't approve of what Hitler was doing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I believe it was in 1936 that Bernhard Rust became the Minister of Education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hitler had an incredible knack to always find the right-- I can't use any off language here-- but to-- Hitler always, from the bottom 2% of the barrel, he always fished out just the right man for every job.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was absolutely brilliant at finding all these warped minds.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Bernhard Rust, his first speech was something that's well recorded, where he decided that formal education was a total waste of time and was totally unimportant, and it didn't count for anything in the German Reich.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And our teacher let it be known in class that she considered formal education still to be worth something.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She had several visits-- we had a class Nazi, Milla Millville, whose father was a Gauleiter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That means he was a supervisor of all the-- the whole Nazi party was a pyramid, with Hitler the top.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was organized.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it's very interesting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "People don't understand that Hitler used the period from 1923, the Putsch in Munich, when he went to jail for a year and dictated to Rudolf Hess.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Hitler spent from 1923 to 1933, he-- I don't think he slept much.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He organized the country in those 10 years.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
